        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Membership_SetPassword",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to update the password for a user in a membership system. It takes several parameters related to the user and the new password, verifies the user's existence, and updates the password details in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_Membership",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table if the user is found."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving a simple SELECT query to verify user existence and an UPDATE statement to change the password. It does not involve complex logic, loops, or error handling mechanisms."
        }
      ]
    },
